data.description: Unique Tudor-style home on quiet tree-lined boulevard. Tons of character and charm with updated features. Kitchen boasts eat-in kitchen booth with storage, custom cabinets and concrete countertops with recycled glass. In the recent master bath update, we revealed the original brick chimney in the back of the cabinets, and the original shiplap, which is a cute touch. Updated plumbing, electrical and windows. New plumbing includes main drain and water main pipe from meter. New exterior doors. New hardie siding on carriage house. Automatic sprinkler system makes it easy to keep the sticker-free lawn green. Gorgeous original hardwood floors. Foundation repaired recently with 3-year warranty. New insulation in attic. Flex room or fourth bedroom in main house and studio space above the garage give ample storage - especially for this era of house! Finally, there are wonderful neighbors and block parties in this lovely community!
data.whatILove:
My hands-down favorite is the front porch with the view down the tree-lined boulevard that is cool in the summer and warm in the winter! Hanging out on the front porch brings a nostalgia and peace of a past era that I love. 

Also, while I was Initially reluctant to embrace this, the laundry in the bathroom is SO convenient! I want this in every future house!
